{{Infobox recurring event | image = | imagesize = frameless | caption = SITEI | filing = | location = [[Abuja]], [[Nigeria]] | frequency = Annually | first = 2012 | begins = | ends = | last = July 19-20, 2017 | participants = 500 | website = [http://csr-in-action.org/sitei/ SITEI] |}} '''The SITEI (Sustainability in the Extractive Industries) Conference''' is an annual conference and workshop for key stakeholders and industry experts in [[natural resource#extraction|extractive industries]], which has been held in [[Abuja]], [[Nigeria]], since 2012.<ref name="SITEI">{{cite web|url=https://www.vanguardngr.com/2017/07/csr-action-partners-neiti-nnpc-others-host-sitei-2017/ |title=CSR-in-Action partners NEITI, NNPC, others to host SITEI 2017|website=Vanguard |date=2017-07-10 |accessdate=2018-03-16}}</ref><ref name="SITEI2">{{cite web|url=https://www.dailytrust.com.ng/news/business/downstream-oil-sector-has-10bn-investments-deficit--kachikwu/206277.html |title=Downstream oil sector has $10bn investments deficit – Kachikwu|website=Daily Trust |date=2017-07-20 |accessdate=2018-03-16}}</ref>
==History==
The SITEI Conference was established together with the Deputy [[Canadian High Commissions|High Commission of Canada]] in October 2012, in [[Lagos]].<ref name="SITEI" /> Over the years, the conferences have been attended by business executives, the most senior government officers for the industries, and the representatives of various organizations.<ref name="SITEI3">{{cite web|url=https://www.bellanaija.com/2017/08/6th-sustainability-in-the-extractive-industries-sitei-conference/ |title=CSR-in-Action’s SITEI 2017 hosts Honourable Ministers Dr. Ibe Kachikwu & Dr. Kayode Fayemi|website=Bella Naija |date=2017-08-07 |accessdate=2018-03-16}}</ref><ref name="SITEI4">{{cite web|url=https://www.premiumtimesng.com/business/business-news/210419-nigeria-award-coal-mining-licenses-power-generating-firms.html |title=Nigeria to award coal mining licenses to only power generating firms|website=Premium Times |date=2016-09-14 |accessdate=2018-03-16}}</ref>
At the 2015 conference, all the stakeholders including the [[Federal government of Nigeria|Nigerian government]] endorsed plans to develop the [[mining industry of Nigeria]].<ref name="SITEI9">{{cite web|url=https://steelguru.com/mining/plans-to-develop-nigerian-mining-sector-endorsed/440275 |title=Plans to develop Nigerian mining sector endorsed|website=Steel Guru |date=2015-12-01 |accessdate=2018-03-16}}</ref> The 2017 conference grew to two days, featuring 25 speakers from the sector and 500 senior executives.<ref name="SITEI" />
The conferences have been organized by sustainability consultancy CSR-in-Action in partnership with NEITI and the Nigerian Government Chapter of the global Extractive Industries Transparency Initiative (EITI).<ref name="SITEI7">{{cite web|url=http://www.mining.com/web/sitei-2015-produces-communique-to-chart-a-course-for-the-sustainable-development-of-the-extractive-industries-in-nigeria/ |title=SITEI 2015 produces communique to chart a course for the sustainable development of the extractive industries in Nigeria|website=Mining.com |date=2015-11-23 |accessdate=2018-03-16}}</ref> The main conveners have been Bekeme Masade of CSR-in-Action and Meka Olowola of Zenera Consulting, who is chairman of the SITEI Committee.<ref name="SITEI5">{{cite web|url=https://www.dailytrust.com.ng/news/general/experts-to-fg-amend-constitution-to-allow-states-own-mineral-resources/207171.html |title=Experts to FG: Amend constitution to allow states own mineral resources|website=Daily Trust |date=2017-07-26 |accessdate=2018-03-16}}</ref><ref name="SITEI6">{{cite web|url=https://www.vanguardngr.com/2017/09/indigenous-oil-gas-companies-coming-age-meka-olowola/ |title=Indigenous oil and gas companies are coming of age – Meka Olowola|website=Vanguard |date=2017-09-23 |accessdate=2018-03-16}}</ref>
